17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 14-127 of Title 47, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 The Department of Transportation is authorized to increase any
22 oversize- or overweight-related permit fees found in its
23 administrative rules including, but not limited to:
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3443 Page 2

1 1. Special Over-height Trailer Permit for Limited Travel
2 thirty-day (30-day) permit;
3 2. Longer Combination Vehicle Annual Permit; and
4 3. Special Over-height Trailer Permit for Limited Travel Annual
5 Permit.
6 The Department shall use a formula for calculating the changes
7 to the fees using a cost-of-living adjustment through the year 2024.
8 When collecting the fees authorized under the provisions of this
9 section, the Department shall deposit the amount of the difference
10 between the fees as of the effective date of this act and the
11 increased fees authorized by this section to the credit of the
12 Rebuilding Oklahoma Access and Driver Safety Fund.
13 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 14-103, as
14 amended by Section 3, Chapter 116, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
15 Section 14-103), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 14-103. A. Except as otherwise provided for by this
17 chapter, no vehicle, with or without load, shall have a total
18 outside width in excess of one hundred two (102) inches excluding:
19 1. Tire bulge;
20 2. Approved safety devices;
21 3. A retracted awning with a width of eight (8) inches or less
22 or other appurtenance of four (4) inches or less which is attached
23 to the side of a recreational vehicle, as defined in Section 1102 of
24 this title; and
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3443 Page 3

1 4. Pins used as a safety precaution or as a load-assisting
2 device if the pins do not extend the overall width of the vehicle
3 beyond nine (9) feet. The State of Oklahoma hereby declares it has
4 determined, in accordance with 23 C.F.R., Section 658.15, that such
5 pins are necessary for the safe and efficient operation of motor
6 vehicles.
7 The provisions of this subsection shall not apply to any person
8 engaged in the hauling of round baled hay with a total outside width
9 of eleven (11) feet or less when the hay is owned by such person and
10 is being hauled for any purpose other than resale. The provisions
11 of this subsection shall also not apply to any county official or
12 employee engaged in the hauling or pulling of a trailer or equipment
13 owned by the county on the county roads of such county.
14 B. Except as otherwise provided for by this chapter:
15 1. No vehicle, with or without load, shall exceed a height of
16 thirteen and one-half (13 1/2) feet on any county road, or fourteen
17 (14) feet on any turnpike, interstate, U.S. or state highway, unless
18 a greater height is authorized by a special permit issued by the
19 Executive Director of the Department of Transportation or an
20 authorized representative of the Department of Transportation
21 specifying the highways to be used, consistent with public
22 convenience and safety. The prohibitions on movement as prescribed
23 in subsection F of Section 14-101 of this title and paragraph 1 of
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3443 Page 4

1 subs ection G of Section 14-101 of this title shall not apply to
2 vehicles operated pursuant to such permits;
3 2. An official state bridge vertical clearance map providing
4 clearance heights as posted for bridges on the interstate, U.S. and
5 state highway systems shall be available on the Oklahoma Department
6 of Transportation website; and
7 3. Operators and owners of vehicles which exceed or have loads
8 which exceed thirteen and one-half (13 1/2) feet shall be held
9 liable for all damages to any part of structures spanning the
10 highway or damages suffered by other affected parties caused by the
11 vehicle or load exceeding the posted height.
