1 SECTION 11. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 14-127 of Title 47, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The Oklahoma Department of Transportation is authorized to
5 increase any oversize or overweight related permit fees found in its
6 administrative rules including, but not limited to:
7 1. Special Overheight Trailer Permit for Limited Travel Thirty-
8 day (30-day) Permit;
9 2. Longer Combination Annual Permit; and
10 3. Special Overheight Trailer Permit for Limited Travel Annual
11 Permit. The Department shall use a formula for calculating the
12 changes to the fees using a cost of living adjustment through the
13 year 2024.
14 SECTION 12. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 14-103, as
15 amended by Section 3, Chapter 116, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
16 Section 14-103), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 14-103. A. Except as otherwise provided for by this
18 chapter, no vehicle, with or without load, shall have a total
19 outside width in excess of one hundred two (102) inches excluding:
